{"html": "<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:4.571em;font-weight:bold;font-family:\"Segoe UI Historic\",\"Noto Sans Phoenician\",\"Noto Serif\",\"Arial Unicode MS\",serif\">𐤉𐤄𐤅𐤄</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.905em;font-weight:bold\">THE ANCIENT COVENANT RECORD</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.238em\">Volume One — Part One</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#666666;font-size:1.048em\">The Book of Bereshit</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:3.048em;font-weight:bold\">BERESHIT</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:1.333em\">In the Beginning — Creation Through the Tower of Babel</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:1.048em;font-weight:bold\">Chapters 1 through 11</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#666666;font-size:0.905em\">In the Beginning Creator Created the Heavens and the Earth — The Creation of Man and Woman — The Fall — Qa'in and Hevel — The Genealogy of Adam — Chanokh Walked With Creator and Was Not — The Flood — The Covenant of the Rainbow — The Tower of Babel</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.905em;font-weight:bold\">PRIMARY MANUSCRIPT AUTHORITIES</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em\">Dead Sea Scrolls — 4QGen-a through 4QGen-j — Multiple Cave 4 Manuscripts</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em\">Ethiopian Orit Ge'ez — Complete Canon — Primary Witness</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em\">Masoretic Text — Referenced as Variant Only</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em\">YHWH and The Creator only</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold\">COMPARATIVE NOTES AT END OF EVERY CHAPTER</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#666666;font-size:0.762em\">DSS  ·  ORIT GE'EZ  ·  MASORETIC VARIANT  ·  CRITICAL NOTE</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#777777;font-size:0.762em;font-family:\"Segoe UI Historic\",\"Noto Sans Phoenician\",\"Noto Serif\",\"Arial Unicode MS\",serif\">YHWH / 𐤉𐤄𐤅𐤄 and The Creator only — no substitute titles</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#777777;font-size:0.762em\">All personal names in original Hebrew form throughout</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center;border-top:1.5px solid #888888;border-bottom:1.5px solid #888888;padding:0.35em 0;margin:0.6em 0\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">BERESHIT — CREATION AND THE PRIMORDIAL HISTORY — CHAPTERS 1 THROUGH 11</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-bottom:1.5px solid #666666;padding-bottom:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#222222;font-size:1.333em;font-weight:bold\">BERESHIT — CHAPTER 1  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:1.048em;font-style:italic\">The Creation of the Heavens and the Earth</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">1  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">In the beginning The Creator created the heavens and the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">2  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The earth was without form and void, and darkness was over the face of the deep. And the Spirit of The Creator was hovering over the face of the waters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">3  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator said: Let there be light, and there was light.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">4  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator saw that the light was good. And The Creator separated the light from the darkness.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">5  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The Creator called the light Day, and the darkness he called Night. And there was evening and there was morning — the first day.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">6  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator said: Let there be an expanse in the midst of the waters, and let it separate the waters from the waters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">7  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator made the expanse and separated the waters that were under the expanse from the waters that were above the expanse. And it was so.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">8  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator called the expanse Heaven. And there was evening and there was morning — the second day.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">9  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator said: Let the waters under the heavens be gathered together into one place, and let the dry land appear. And it was so.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">10  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The Creator called the dry land Earth, and the waters that were gathered together he called Seas. And The Creator saw that it was good.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">11  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator said: Let the earth sprout vegetation, plants yielding seed, and fruit trees bearing fruit in which is their seed, each according to its kind. And it was so.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">12  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The earth brought forth vegetation, plants yielding seed according to their own kinds, and trees bearing fruit in which is their seed, each according to its kind. And The Creator saw that it was good.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">13  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And there was evening and there was morning — the third day.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">14  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator said: Let there be lights in the expanse of the heavens to separate the day from the night. And let them be for signs and for seasons, and for days and years.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">15  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And let them be lights in the expanse of the heavens to give light upon the earth. And it was so.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">16  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator made the two great lights — the greater light to rule the day and the lesser light to rule the night — and the stars.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">17  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator set them in the expanse of the heavens to give light on the earth,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">18  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">To rule over the day and over the night, and to separate the light from the darkness. And The Creator saw that it was good.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">19  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And there was evening and there was morning — the fourth day.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">20  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator said: Let the waters swarm with swarms of living creatures, and let birds fly above the earth across the expanse of the heavens.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">21  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">So The Creator created the great sea creatures and every living creature that moves, with which the waters swarm, according to their kinds, and every winged bird according to its kind. And The Creator saw that it was good.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">22  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator blessed them, saying: Be fruitful and multiply and fill the waters in the seas, and let birds multiply on the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">23  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And there was evening and there was morning — the fifth day.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">24  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator said: Let the earth bring forth living creatures according to their kinds — livestock and creeping things and beasts of the earth according to their kinds. And it was so.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">25  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator made the beasts of the earth according to their kinds and the livestock according to their kinds, and everything that creeps on the ground according to its kind. And The Creator saw that it was good.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">26  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then The Creator said: Let us make man in our image, after our likeness. And let them have dominion over the fish of the sea and over the birds of the heavens and over the livestock and over all the earth and over every creeping thing that creeps on the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">27  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">So The Creator created man in his own image, in the image of The Creator he created him — male and female he created them.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">28  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator blessed them. And The Creator said to them: Be fruitful and multiply and fill the earth and subdue it, and have dominion over the fish of the sea and over the birds of the heavens and over every living thing that moves on the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">29  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator said: Behold, I have given you every plant yielding seed that is on the face of all the earth, and every tree with seed in its fruit. You shall have them for food.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">30  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And to every beast of the earth and to every bird of the heavens and to everything that creeps on the earth, everything that has the breath of life, I have given every green plant for food. And it was so.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">31  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator saw everything that he had made, and behold, it was very good. And there was evening and there was morning — the sixth day.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-top:1px solid #aaaaaa;padding-top:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.905em;font-weight:bold\">COMPARATIVE MANUSCRIPT NOTES</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1A5276;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[DSS]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">4QGena (4Q1) and 4QGenb (4Q2) preserve portions of Chapter 1. The creation account is attested in multiple Cave 4 manuscripts. Text aligns closely between DSS and Orit Ge'ez in this chapter.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1E8449;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[ORIT GE'EZ]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">The Ethiopian Orit Ge'ez preserves Chapter 1 in full. The Ge'ez reads identical theology — The Creator speaking creation into existence over six days. No variation in the sequence of created things.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#7D6608;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[MASORETIC VARIANT]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">Masoretic text reads identically to the DSS for this chapter. The divine name Elohim — used throughout Chapter 1 in all manuscript traditions — is rendered as The Creator throughout this compilation per the foundational rule established. The YHWH form appears from Chapter 2 onward in the Hebrew texts.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#6E2F8A;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[CRITICAL NOTE]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">Verse 1:26 — Let us make man in our image. The plural us and our is present in the Hebrew DSS. The ancient Hebrew theology understands this as YHWH speaking among his divine council — the heavenly host. The Book of Chanokh and Yovelim both confirm the existence of this council. Yovelim 2:2 states the angels of the presence were created on Day One — they are present when Day Six begins.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-bottom:1.5px solid #666666;padding-bottom:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#222222;font-size:1.333em;font-weight:bold\">BERESHIT — CHAPTER 2  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:1.048em;font-style:italic\">The Seventh Day — The Garden of Eden — The First Man and Woman</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">1  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Thus the heavens and the earth were finished, and all the host of them.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">2  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And on the seventh day The Creator finished his work that he had done, and he rested on the seventh day from all his work that he had done.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">3  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">So The Creator blessed the seventh day and made it holy, because on it The Creator rested from all his work that he had done in creation.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">4  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">These are the generations of the heavens and the earth when they were created, in the day that YHWH The Creator made the earth and the heavens.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">5  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When no bush of the field was yet in the land and no small plant of the field had yet sprung up — for YHWH The Creator had not yet caused it to rain on the land, and there was no man to work the ground —</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">6  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And a mist was going up from the land and was watering the whole face of the ground.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">7  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then YHWH The Creator formed the man of dust from the ground and breathed into his nostrils the breath of life, and the man became a living creature.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">8  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And YHWH The Creator planted a garden in Eden, in the east, and there he put the man whom he had formed.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">9  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And out of the ground YHWH The Creator made to spring up every tree that is pleasant to the sight and good for food. The tree of life was in the midst of the garden, and the tree of the knowledge of good and evil.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">10  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">A river flowed out of Eden to water the garden, and there it divided and became four rivers.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">11  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The name of the first is Pishon. It is the one that flowed around the whole land of Havilah, where there is gold.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">12  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And the gold of that land is good — bdellium and onyx stone are there.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">13  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The name of the second river is Gihon. It is the one that flowed around the whole land of Kush.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">14  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And the name of the third river is the Tigris, which flows east of Asshur. And the fourth river is the Euphrates.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">15  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">YHWH The Creator took the man and put him in the Garden of Eden to work it and keep it.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">16  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And YHWH The Creator commanded the man, saying: You may surely eat of every tree of the garden,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">17  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">But of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil you shall not eat, for in the day that you eat of it you shall surely die.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">18  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then YHWH The Creator said: It is not good that the man should be alone — I will make him a helper fit for him.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">19  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Now out of the ground YHWH The Creator had formed every beast of the field and every bird of the heavens and brought them to the man to see what he would call them. And whatever the man called every living creature, that was its name.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">20  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The man gave names to all livestock and to the birds of the heavens and to every beast of the field. But for Adam there was not found a helper fit for him.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">21  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">So YHWH The Creator caused a deep sleep to fall upon the man, and while he slept took one of his ribs and closed up its place with flesh.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">22  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And the rib that YHWH The Creator had taken from the man he made into a woman and brought her to the man.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">23  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then the man said: This at last is bone of my bones and flesh of my flesh — she shall be called Ishah, because she was taken out of Ish.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">24  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Therefore a man shall leave his father and his mother and hold fast to his wife, and they shall become one flesh.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">25  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And the man and his wife were both naked and were not ashamed.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-top:1px solid #aaaaaa;padding-top:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.905em;font-weight:bold\">COMPARATIVE MANUSCRIPT NOTES</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1A5276;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[DSS]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">4QGena and 4QGenb preserve portions of Chapter 2. The Genesis Apocryphon — 1QapGen — expands the garden narrative with additional Aramaic detail not present in the Torah text itself.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1E8449;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[ORIT GE'EZ]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">The Orit Ge'ez preserves Chapter 2 in full. The Ge'ez text includes the detail that the Gihon river flows around the whole land of Kush — confirming the African geography of Eden's river system.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#7D6608;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[MASORETIC VARIANT]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">No significant variants from the DSS in this chapter.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#6E2F8A;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[CRITICAL NOTE]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">Verse 2:7 — YHWH formed the man of dust from the ground and breathed into his nostrils the breath of life. The Hebrew word is nishmat — the breath-soul. This is distinct from ruach — spirit. Man receives both. The nishmat is the unique divine impartation that distinguishes humanity from all other creatures. No other creature receives this breath directly from YHWH's own being.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-bottom:1.5px solid #666666;padding-bottom:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#222222;font-size:1.333em;font-weight:bold\">BERESHIT — CHAPTER 3  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:1.048em;font-style:italic\">The Serpent — The Fall — The Exile from Eden</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">1  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Now the serpent was more crafty than any other beast of the field that YHWH The Creator had made. He said to the woman: Did The Creator actually say, you shall not eat of any tree in the garden?</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">2  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And the woman said to the serpent: We may eat of the fruit of the trees in the garden,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">3  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">But The Creator said: You shall not eat of the fruit of the tree that is in the midst of the garden, neither shall you touch it, lest you die.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">4  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">But the serpent said to the woman: You will not surely die.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">5  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">For The Creator knows that when you eat of it your eyes will be opened, and you will be like The Creator, knowing good and evil.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">6  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">So when the woman saw that the tree was good for food, and that it was a delight to the eyes, and that the tree was to be desired to make one wise, she took of its fruit and ate, and she also gave some to her husband who was with her, and he ate.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">7  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then the eyes of both were opened, and they knew that they were naked. And they sewed fig leaves together and made themselves loincloths.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">8  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And they heard the sound of YHWH The Creator walking in the garden in the cool of the day, and the man and his wife hid themselves from the presence of YHWH The Creator among the trees of the garden.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">9  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">But YHWH The Creator called to the man and said to him: Where are you?</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">10  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And he said: I heard the sound of you in the garden, and I was afraid, because I was naked, and I hid myself.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">11  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">He said: Who told you that you were naked? Have you eaten of the tree of which I commanded you not to eat?</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">12  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The man said: The woman whom you gave to be with me, she gave me fruit of the tree, and I ate.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">13  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then YHWH The Creator said to the woman: What is this that you have done? The woman said: The serpent deceived me, and I ate.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">14  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">YHWH The Creator said to the serpent: Because you have done this, cursed are you above all livestock and above all beasts of the field. On your belly you shall go, and dust you shall eat all the days of your life.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">15  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">I will put enmity between you and the woman, and between your offspring and her offspring — he shall bruise your head, and you shall bruise his heel.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">16  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">To the woman he said: I will surely multiply your pain in childbearing — in pain you shall bring forth children. Your desire shall be for your husband, and he shall rule over you.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">17  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And to Adam he said: Because you have listened to the voice of your wife and have eaten of the tree of which I commanded you, cursed is the ground because of you — in pain you shall eat of it all the days of your life.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">18  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Thorns and thistles it shall bring forth for you, and you shall eat the plants of the field.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">19  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">By the sweat of your face you shall eat bread, till you return to the ground, for out of it you were taken — for you are dust, and to dust you shall return.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">20  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The man called his wife's name Chavah — because she was the mother of all living.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">21  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And YHWH The Creator made for Adam and for his wife garments of skins and clothed them.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">22  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then YHWH The Creator said: Behold, the man has become like one of us in knowing good and evil. Now, lest he reach out his hand and take also of the tree of life and eat, and live forever —</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">23  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Therefore YHWH The Creator sent him out from the Garden of Eden to work the ground from which he was taken.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">24  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">He drove out the man, and at the east of the Garden of Eden he placed the cherubim and a flaming sword that turned every way to guard the way to the tree of life.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-top:1px solid #aaaaaa;padding-top:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.905em;font-weight:bold\">COMPARATIVE MANUSCRIPT NOTES</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1A5276;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[DSS]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">4QGena preserves portions of Chapter 3. The expulsion from the Garden is attested in the DSS fragments.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1E8449;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[ORIT GE'EZ]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">The Orit Ge'ez preserves Chapter 3 in full. The woman is named Havvat — Chavah — in verse 3:20, meaning mother of all living.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#7D6608;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[MASORETIC VARIANT]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">No significant variants in this chapter.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#6E2F8A;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[CRITICAL NOTE]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">Verse 3:15 — enmity between the serpent's offspring and the woman's offspring. The Book of Chanokh Chapters 6-11 expands this enmity — the Watcher angels who descended and corrupted both the human line and the animal world represent the continuation of this spiritual war. The seed of the serpent is understood in the ancient Hebrew tradition as a lineage of corruption, not merely a literal animal.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-bottom:1.5px solid #666666;padding-bottom:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#222222;font-size:1.333em;font-weight:bold\">BERESHIT — CHAPTER 4  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:1.048em;font-style:italic\">Qayin and Hevel — The First Murder — The Line of Qayin</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">1  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Now Adam knew Chavah his wife, and she conceived and bore Qayin, saying: I have gotten a man with the help of YHWH.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">2  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And again, she bore his brother Hevel. Now Hevel was a keeper of sheep, and Qayin a worker of the ground.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">3  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">In the course of time Qayin brought to YHWH an offering of the fruit of the ground,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">4  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Hevel also brought of the firstborn of his flock and of their fat portions. And YHWH had regard for Hevel and his offering,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">5  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">But for Qayin and his offering he had no regard. So Qayin was very angry, and his face fell.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">6  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">YHWH said to Qayin: Why are you angry, and why has your face fallen?</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">7  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">If you do well, will you not be accepted? And if you do not do well, sin is crouching at the door. Its desire is for you, but you must rule over it.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">8  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Qayin spoke to Hevel his brother: Come, let us go out to the field. And when they were in the field, Qayin rose up against his brother Hevel and killed him.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">9  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then YHWH said to Qayin: Where is Hevel your brother? He said: I do not know — am I my brother's keeper?</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">10  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And YHWH said: What have you done? The voice of your brother's blood is crying to me from the ground.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">11  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And now you are cursed from the ground, which has opened its mouth to receive your brother's blood from your hand.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">12  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When you work the ground, it shall no longer yield to you its strength. You shall be a fugitive and a wanderer on the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">13  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Qayin said to YHWH: My punishment is greater than I can bear.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">14  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Behold, you have driven me today away from the ground, and from your face I shall be hidden. I shall be a fugitive and a wanderer on the earth, and whoever finds me will kill me.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">15  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then YHWH said to him: Not so — if anyone kills Qayin, vengeance shall be taken on him sevenfold. And YHWH put a mark on Qayin, lest any who found him should attack him.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">16  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then Qayin went away from the presence of YHWH and settled in the land of Nod, east of Eden.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">17  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Qayin knew his wife, and she conceived and bore Chanokh. When he built a city, he called the name of the city after the name of his son, Chanokh.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">18  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">To Chanokh was born Irad, and Irad fathered Mechuyael, and Mechuyael fathered Metushael, and Metushael fathered Lamekh.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">19  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Lamekh took two wives. The name of the one was Adah, and the name of the other Tzillah.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">20  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Adah bore Yaval — he was the father of those who dwell in tents and have livestock.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">21  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">His brother's name was Yuval — he was the father of all those who play the lyre and pipe.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">22  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Tzillah also bore Tuval-Qayin — he was the forger of all instruments of bronze and iron. The sister of Tuval-Qayin was Naamah.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">23  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Lamekh said to his wives: Adah and Tzillah, hear my voice — I have killed a man for wounding me, a young man for striking me.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">24  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">If Qayin's revenge is sevenfold, then Lamekh's is seventy-sevenfold.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">25  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Adam knew his wife again, and she bore a son and called his name Shet, for she said: The Creator has appointed for me another offspring instead of Hevel, for Qayin killed him.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">26  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">To Shet also a son was born, and he called his name Enosh. At that time people began to call upon the name of YHWH.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-top:1px solid #aaaaaa;padding-top:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.905em;font-weight:bold\">COMPARATIVE MANUSCRIPT NOTES</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1A5276;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[DSS]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">4QGena and the Genesis Apocryphon (1QapGen) preserve portions of Chapter 4. The DSS text of verse 4:8 includes the full speech of Qayin — Come, let us go out to the field — which is absent from the standard Masoretic Hebrew but present in the Septuagint, the Samaritan Pentateuch, the Peshitta, and the Orit Ge'ez. This is the DSS/Orit reading followed here.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1E8449;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[ORIT GE'EZ]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">The Orit Ge'ez preserves the full speech of Qayin to Hevel in verse 4:8, confirming the DSS reading. The Masoretic text omits this speech creating an incomplete sentence. The DSS and Orit agreement is the textual authority here.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#7D6608;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[MASORETIC VARIANT]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">VARIANT — verse 4:8: The Masoretic text reads Qayin spoke to Hevel his brother but omits what was said, creating a grammatical gap. This is one of the clearest cases where the DSS and Orit Ge'ez together correct a Masoretic omission. The DSS/Orit reading is used throughout this compilation.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#6E2F8A;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[CRITICAL NOTE]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">Verse 4:26 — at that time people began to call upon the name of YHWH. The name YHWH was known and called upon from the generation of Enosh — Adam's grandson. Yovelim confirms this and states that Chanokh — of the righteous Shet line — was the first to write the name down formally and teach it to others.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-bottom:1.5px solid #666666;padding-bottom:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#222222;font-size:1.333em;font-weight:bold\">BERESHIT — CHAPTER 5  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:1.048em;font-style:italic\">The Generations from Adam to Noakh — Chanokh Taken by The Creator</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">1  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">This is the book of the generations of Adam. When The Creator created man, he made him in the likeness of The Creator.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">2  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Male and female he created them, and he blessed them and named them Man when they were created.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">3  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Adam had lived 130 years, he fathered a son in his own likeness, after his image, and named him Shet.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">4  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The days of Adam after he fathered Shet were 800 years, and he had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">5  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Thus all the days that Adam lived were 930 years, and he died.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">6  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Shet had lived 105 years, he fathered Enosh.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">7  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Shet lived after he fathered Enosh 807 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">8  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Thus all the days of Shet were 912 years, and he died.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">9  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Enosh had lived 90 years, he fathered Qeynan.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">10  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Enosh lived after he fathered Qeynan 815 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">11  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Thus all the days of Enosh were 905 years, and he died.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">12  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Qeynan had lived 70 years, he fathered Mahalalel.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">13  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Qeynan lived after he fathered Mahalalel 840 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">14  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Thus all the days of Qeynan were 910 years, and he died.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">15  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Mahalalel had lived 65 years, he fathered Yered.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">16  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Mahalalel lived after he fathered Yered 830 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">17  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Thus all the days of Mahalalel were 895 years, and he died.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">18  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Yered had lived 162 years, he fathered Chanokh.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">19  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Yered lived after he fathered Chanokh 800 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">20  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Thus all the days of Yered were 962 years, and he died.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">21  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Chanokh had lived 65 years, he fathered Metushelakh.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">22  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Chanokh walked with The Creator after he fathered Metushelakh 300 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">23  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Thus all the days of Chanokh were 365 years.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">24  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Chanokh walked with The Creator, and he was not, for The Creator took him.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">25  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Metushelakh had lived 187 years, he fathered Lamekh.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">26  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Metushelakh lived after he fathered Lamekh 782 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">27  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Thus all the days of Metushelakh were 969 years, and he died.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">28  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Lamekh had lived 182 years, he fathered a son</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">29  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And called his name Noakh, saying: Out of the ground that YHWH has cursed, this one shall bring us relief from our work and from the painful toil of our hands.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">30  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Lamekh lived after he fathered Noakh 595 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">31  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Thus all the days of Lamekh were 777 years, and he died.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">32  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">After Noakh was 500 years old, Noakh fathered Shem, Cham, and Yafet.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-top:1px solid #aaaaaa;padding-top:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.905em;font-weight:bold\">COMPARATIVE MANUSCRIPT NOTES</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1A5276;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[DSS]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">4QGena preserves portions of the genealogy of Chapter 5. The ages of the patriarchs in the DSS text preserve the same sequence as in the Orit Ge'ez.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1E8449;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[ORIT GE'EZ]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">The Orit Ge'ez preserves the complete genealogy of Chapter 5 in full.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#7D6608;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[MASORETIC VARIANT]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">The ages given in the Masoretic text for the pre-flood patriarchs differ from the Septuagint tradition in some cases. Where DSS evidence exists it is followed. For this genealogy no significant DSS variant from the sequence recorded here.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#6E2F8A;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[CRITICAL NOTE]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">Verse 5:29 — Noakh means rest or relief. Lamekh names his son prophetically — this one shall bring us relief from the cursed ground. The connection to Bereshit 3:17 where the ground was cursed because of Adam is explicit. Noakh's survival of the flood and the subsequent covenant removing the curse from the ground fulfills Lamekh's naming prophecy directly.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-bottom:1.5px solid #666666;padding-bottom:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#222222;font-size:1.333em;font-weight:bold\">BERESHIT — CHAPTER 6  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:1.048em;font-style:italic\">The Sons of The Creator — The Nephilim — YHWH Resolves to Send the Flood</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">1  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When man began to multiply on the face of the land and daughters were born to them,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">2  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The sons of The Creator saw that the daughters of man were attractive. And they took as their wives any they chose.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">3  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then YHWH said: My Spirit shall not abide in man forever, for he is flesh — his days shall be 120 years.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">4  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The Nephilim were on the earth in those days, and also afterward, when the sons of The Creator came in to the daughters of man and they bore children to them. These were the mighty men who were of old, the men of renown.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">5  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">YHWH saw that the wickedness of man was great in the earth, and that every intention of the thoughts of his heart was only evil continually.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">6  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And YHWH regretted that he had made man on the earth, and it grieved him to his heart.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">7  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">So YHWH said: I will blot out man whom I have created from the face of the land, man and animals and creeping things and birds of the heavens, for I am sorry that I have made them.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">8  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">But Noakh found favor in the eyes of YHWH.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">9  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">These are the generations of Noakh. Noakh was a righteous man, blameless in his generation. Noakh walked with The Creator.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">10  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Noakh had three sons: Shem, Cham, and Yafet.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">11  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Now the earth was corrupt in The Creator's sight, and the earth was filled with violence.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">12  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator saw the earth, and behold, it was corrupt, for all flesh had corrupted their way on the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">13  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator said to Noakh: I have determined to make an end of all flesh, for the earth is filled with violence through them. Behold, I will destroy them with the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">14  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Make yourself an ark of gopher wood. Make rooms in the ark, and cover it inside and out with pitch.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">15  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">This is how you are to make it: the length of the ark 300 cubits, its breadth 50 cubits, and its height 30 cubits.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">16  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Make a roof for the ark, and finish it to a cubit above, and set the door of the ark in its side. Make it with lower, second, and third decks.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">17  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">For behold, I will bring a flood of waters upon the earth to destroy all flesh in which is the breath of life under heaven. Everything that is on the earth shall die.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">18  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">But I will establish my covenant with you, and you shall come into the ark, you, your sons, your wife, and your sons' wives with you.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">19  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And of every living thing of all flesh, you shall bring two of every sort into the ark to keep them alive with you. They shall be male and female.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">20  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Of the birds according to their kinds, and of the animals according to their kinds, of every creeping thing of the ground, according to its kind, two of every sort shall come in to you to keep them alive.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">21  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Also take with you every sort of food that is eaten, and store it up. It shall serve as food for you and for them.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">22  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Noakh did this — he did all that The Creator commanded him.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-top:1px solid #aaaaaa;padding-top:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.905em;font-weight:bold\">COMPARATIVE MANUSCRIPT NOTES</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1A5276;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[DSS]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">4QGena and 4QGenb preserve portions of Chapter 6. The dimensions of the ark and YHWH's speech to Noakh are attested in the DSS fragments. The Genesis Apocryphon — 1QapGen — expands the ark narrative with additional detail in Aramaic.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1E8449;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[ORIT GE'EZ]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">The Orit Ge'ez preserves Chapter 6 in full. The Ge'ez text of verse 6:4 reads the Nephilim were on the earth in those days — the Giant offspring of the Watcher unions described in Chanokh Chapters 6-8.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#7D6608;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[MASORETIC VARIANT]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">The phrase sons of The Creator in verse 6:2 and 6:4 is preserved identically in the DSS, the Orit Ge'ez, and the Masoretic text. Some later traditions attempted to re-interpret this phrase as sons of rulers or nobility — the DSS and Orit Ge'ez make clear these are heavenly beings, the Watchers of the Book of Chanokh. The DSS reading is the authority here.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#6E2F8A;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[CRITICAL NOTE]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">Verse 6:4 — the Nephilim. This is the Hebrew word for the Giant offspring of the Watchers — from the root naphal, to fall. The Book of Chanokh Chapters 7-8 is the full account of what Bereshit 6:1-4 describes in four verses. Chanokh provides the names, the count of 200, the location at Mount Hermon, and the specific corruptions each Watcher taught. Bereshit and Chanokh are two parts of one account.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-bottom:1.5px solid #666666;padding-bottom:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#222222;font-size:1.333em;font-weight:bold\">BERESHIT — CHAPTER 7  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:1.048em;font-style:italic\">Noakh Enters the Ark — The Flood Begins</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">1  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then YHWH said to Noakh: Go into the ark, you and all your household, for I have seen that you are righteous before me in this generation.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">2  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Take with you seven pairs of all clean animals, the male and his mate, and a pair of the animals that are not clean, the male and his mate,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">3  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And seven pairs of the birds of the heavens also, male and female, to keep their offspring alive on the face of all the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">4  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">For in seven days I will send rain on the earth forty days and forty nights, and every living thing that I have made I will blot out from the face of the ground.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">5  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Noakh did all that YHWH had commanded him.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">6  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Noakh was six hundred years old when the flood of waters came upon the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">7  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Noakh and his sons and his wife and his sons' wives with him went into the ark to escape the waters of the flood.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">8  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Of clean animals, and of animals that are not clean, and of birds, and of everything that creeps on the ground,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">9  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Two and two, male and female, went into the ark with Noakh, as The Creator had commanded Noakh.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">10  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And after seven days the waters of the flood came upon the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">11  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">In the six hundredth year of Noakh's life, in the second month, on the seventeenth day of the month, on that day all the fountains of the great deep burst forth, and the windows of the heavens were opened.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">12  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And rain fell upon the earth forty days and forty nights.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">13  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">On the very same day Noakh and his sons, Shem and Cham and Yafet, and Noakh's wife and the three wives of his sons with them entered the ark,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">14  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">They and every beast, according to its kind, and all the livestock according to their kinds, and every creeping thing that creeps on the earth, according to its kind, and every bird, according to its kind, every winged creature.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">15  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">They went into the ark with Noakh, two and two of all flesh in which there was the breath of life.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">16  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And those that entered, male and female of all flesh, went in as The Creator had commanded him. And YHWH shut him in.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">17  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The flood continued forty days on the earth. The waters increased and bore up the ark, and it rose high above the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">18  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The waters prevailed and increased greatly on the earth, and the ark floated on the face of the waters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">19  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And the waters prevailed so mightily on the earth that all the high mountains under the whole heaven were covered.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">20  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The waters prevailed above the mountains, covering them fifteen cubits deep.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">21  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And all flesh died that moved on the earth, birds, livestock, beasts, all swarming creatures that swarm on the earth, and all mankind.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">22  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Everything on the dry land in whose nostrils was the breath of life died.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">23  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">He blotted out every living thing that was on the face of the ground, man and animals and creeping things and birds of the heavens. They were blotted out from the earth. Only Noakh was left, and those who were with him in the ark.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">24  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And the waters prevailed on the earth 150 days.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-top:1px solid #aaaaaa;padding-top:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.905em;font-weight:bold\">COMPARATIVE MANUSCRIPT NOTES</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1A5276;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[DSS]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">4QGena and the Genesis Apocryphon preserve portions of the flood narrative. The 1QapGen Aramaic text expands the account of Noakh entering the ark with additional dialogue not present in the brief Torah text.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1E8449;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[ORIT GE'EZ]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">The Orit Ge'ez preserves Chapter 7 in full.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#7D6608;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[MASORETIC VARIANT]  </span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#6E2F8A;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[CRITICAL NOTE]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">Verse 7:16 — YHWH shut him in. This is one of the most significant details in the flood narrative. Noakh did not close the door himself. YHWH personally sealed the ark. The survival of Noakh's family was not a matter of their own engineering — it was YHWH's direct act of preservation. The same theology runs through the entire covenant record: YHWH is the one who acts, who seals, who preserves.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-bottom:1.5px solid #666666;padding-bottom:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#222222;font-size:1.333em;font-weight:bold\">BERESHIT — CHAPTER 8  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:1.048em;font-style:italic\">The Waters Recede — Noakh Leaves the Ark — The Covenant of the Rainbow</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">1  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">But The Creator remembered Noakh and all the beasts and all the livestock that were with him in the ark. And The Creator made a wind blow over the earth, and the waters subsided.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">2  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The fountains of the deep and the windows of the heavens were closed, the rain from the heavens was restrained,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">3  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And the waters receded from the earth continually. At the end of 150 days the waters had abated.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">4  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And in the seventh month, on the seventeenth day of the month, the ark came to rest on the mountains of Ararat.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">5  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And the waters continued to abate until the tenth month. In the tenth month, on the first day of the month, the tops of the mountains were seen.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">6  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">At the end of forty days Noakh opened the window of the ark that he had made</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">7  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And sent forth a raven. It went to and fro until the waters were dried up from the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">8  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then he sent forth a dove from him, to see if the waters had subsided from the face of the ground.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">9  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">But the dove found no place to set her foot, and she returned to him to the ark, for the waters were still on the face of the whole earth. So he put out his hand and took her and brought her into the ark with him.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">10  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">He waited another seven days, and again he sent forth the dove out of the ark.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">11  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And the dove came back to him in the evening, and behold, in her mouth was a freshly plucked olive leaf. So Noakh knew that the waters had subsided from the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">12  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then he waited another seven days and sent forth the dove, and she did not return to him anymore.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">13  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">In the six hundred and first year, in the first month, the first day of the month, the waters were dried from off the earth. And Noakh removed the covering of the ark and looked, and behold, the face of the ground was dry.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">14  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">In the second month, on the twenty-seventh day of the month, the earth had dried out.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">15  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then The Creator said to Noakh:</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">16  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Go out from the ark, you and your wife, and your sons and your sons' wives with you.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">17  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Bring out with you every living thing that is with you of all flesh — birds and animals and every creeping thing that creeps on the earth — that they may swarm on the earth, and be fruitful and multiply on the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">18  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">So Noakh went out, and his sons and his wife and his sons' wives with him.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">19  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Every beast, every creeping thing, and every bird, everything that moves on the earth, went out by families from the ark.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">20  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then Noakh built an altar to YHWH and took some of every clean animal and some of every clean bird and offered burnt offerings on the altar.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">21  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And when YHWH smelled the pleasing aroma, YHWH said in his heart: I will never again curse the ground because of man, for the intention of man's heart is evil from his youth. Neither will I ever again strike down every living creature as I have done.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">22  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">While the earth remains, seedtime and harvest, cold and heat, summer and winter, day and night, shall not cease.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-top:1px solid #aaaaaa;padding-top:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.905em;font-weight:bold\">COMPARATIVE MANUSCRIPT NOTES</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1A5276;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[DSS]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">4QGena and the Genesis Apocryphon preserve portions of Chapter 8. The 1QapGen Aramaic expands Noakh's words upon leaving the ark with additional thanksgiving not in the brief Torah text.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1E8449;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[ORIT GE'EZ]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">The Orit Ge'ez preserves Chapter 8 in full. Yovelim 6:1-4 expands the altar-building account and states that Noakh celebrated this day as the feast of the firstfruits of the harvest — connecting the landing of the ark to the later feast calendar.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#7D6608;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[MASORETIC VARIANT]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">No significant variants from the DSS in this chapter.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#6E2F8A;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[CRITICAL NOTE]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">Verse 8:21 — YHWH said in his heart: I will never again curse the ground. This is not a public declaration — it is YHWH's inner resolve. The covenant of verse 9 formalizes this resolve externally. The inner decision precedes the public covenant sign. YHWH's mercy was already determined before the rainbow was set in the sky.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-bottom:1.5px solid #666666;padding-bottom:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#222222;font-size:1.333em;font-weight:bold\">BERESHIT — CHAPTER 9  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:1.048em;font-style:italic\">The Noahic Covenant — The Rainbow — The Curse of Kena'an</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">1  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator blessed Noakh and his sons and said to them: Be fruitful and multiply and fill the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">2  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The fear of you and the dread of you shall be upon every beast of the earth and upon every bird of the heavens, upon everything that creeps on the ground and all the fish of the sea. Into your hand they are delivered.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">3  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Every moving thing that lives shall be food for you. And as I gave you the green plants, I give you everything.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">4  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">But you shall not eat flesh with its life, that is, its blood.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">5  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And for your lifeblood I will require a reckoning: from every beast I will require it and from man. From his fellow man I will require a reckoning for the life of man.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">6  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Whoever sheds the blood of man, by man shall his blood be shed, for The Creator made man in his own image.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">7  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And you, be fruitful and multiply, increase greatly on the earth and multiply in it.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">8  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then The Creator said to Noakh and to his sons with him:</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">9  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Behold, I establish my covenant with you and your offspring after you,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">10  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And with every living creature that is with you, the birds, the livestock, and every beast of the earth with you, as many as came out of the ark — it is for every beast of the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">11  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">I establish my covenant with you, that never again shall all flesh be cut off by the waters of the flood, and never again shall there be a flood to destroy the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">12  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And The Creator said: This is the sign of the covenant that I make between me and you and every living creature that is with you, for all future generations:</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">13  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">I have set my bow in the cloud, and it shall be a sign of the covenant between me and the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">14  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When I bring clouds over the earth and the bow is seen in the clouds,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">15  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">I will remember my covenant that is between me and you and every living creature of all flesh. And the waters shall never again become a flood to destroy all flesh.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">16  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When the bow is in the clouds, I will see it and remember the everlasting covenant between The Creator and every living creature of all flesh that is on the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">17  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The Creator said to Noakh: This is the sign of the covenant that I have established between me and all flesh that is on the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">18  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The sons of Noakh who went forth from the ark were Shem, Cham, and Yafet. Cham was the father of Kena'an.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">19  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">These three were the sons of Noakh, and from these the people of the whole earth were dispersed.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">20  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Noakh began to be a man of the soil, and he planted a vineyard.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">21  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">He drank of the wine and became drunk and lay uncovered in his tent.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">22  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Cham, the father of Kena'an, saw the nakedness of his father and told his two brothers outside.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">23  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then Shem and Yafet took a garment, laid it on both their shoulders, and walked backward and covered the nakedness of their father. Their faces were turned backward, and they did not see their father's nakedness.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">24  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Noakh awoke from his wine and knew what his youngest son had done to him,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">25  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">He said: Cursed be Kena'an — a servant of servants shall he be to his brothers.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">26  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">He also said: Blessed be YHWH, the Creator of Shem — and let Kena'an be his servant.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">27  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">May The Creator enlarge Yafet, and let him dwell in the tents of Shem, and let Kena'an be his servant.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">28  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">After the flood Noakh lived 350 years.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">29  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">All the days of Noakh were 950 years, and he died.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-top:1px solid #aaaaaa;padding-top:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.905em;font-weight:bold\">COMPARATIVE MANUSCRIPT NOTES</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1A5276;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[DSS]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">4QGena preserves portions of Chapter 9. The covenant with Noakh and the rainbow sign are attested in the DSS fragments.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1E8449;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[ORIT GE'EZ]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">The Orit Ge'ez preserves Chapter 9 in full. Yovelim 7:20 expands the instruction Noakh gave his descendants at this time — commandments to observe righteousness, honor parents, love neighbors, and guard against fornication and uncleanness.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#7D6608;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[MASORETIC VARIANT]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">No significant variants from the DSS in this chapter.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#6E2F8A;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[CRITICAL NOTE]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">Verse 9:4 — do not eat flesh with its blood. This is the first dietary law in the covenant record — given to all of Noakh's descendants, not only to Yisra'EL. The prohibition on consuming blood applies to all humanity from the time of the Noahic covenant. Vayikra 17:10-14 extends this law explicitly to Yisra'EL and to any stranger dwelling among them.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-bottom:1.5px solid #666666;padding-bottom:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#222222;font-size:1.333em;font-weight:bold\">BERESHIT — CHAPTER 10  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:1.048em;font-style:italic\">The Table of Nations — The Descendants of Noakh</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">1  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">These are the generations of the sons of Noakh, Shem, Cham, and Yafet. Sons were born to them after the flood.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">2  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The sons of Yafet: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Yavan, Tuval, Meshekh, and Tiras.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">3  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The sons of Gomer: Ashkenaz, Rifat, and Togarmah.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">4  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The sons of Yavan: Elishah, Tarshish, the Kittim, and the Dodanim.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">5  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">From these the coastland peoples spread in their lands, each with his own language, by their clans, in their nations.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">6  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The sons of Cham: Kush, Mitzraim, Put, and Kena'an.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">7  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The sons of Kush: Seva, Havilah, Savtah, Ra'amah, and Savtekha. The sons of Ra'amah: Sheva and Dedan.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">8  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Kush fathered Nimrod — he was the first on earth to be a mighty man.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">9  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">He was a mighty hunter before YHWH. Therefore it is said: Like Nimrod a mighty hunter before YHWH.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">10  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The beginning of his kingdom was Bavel, Erekh, Akkad, and Kalneh, in the land of Shinar.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">11  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">From that land he went into Asshur and built Nineveh, Rehovot-Ir, Kelah,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">12  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Resen between Nineveh and Kelah — that is the great city.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">13  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Mitzraim fathered the Ludim, the Anamim, the Lehavim, the Naftuhim,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">14  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The Patrusim, the Kasluhim — from whom the Pelishtim came — and the Kaftarim.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">15  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Kena'an fathered Tzidon his firstborn and Het,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">16  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And the Yevusi, the Emori, the Girgashi,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">17  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The Hivi, the Arki, the Sini,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">18  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The Arvadi, the Tzamari, and the Hamati. Afterward the clans of the Kena'ani dispersed.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">19  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And the territory of the Kena'ani extended from Tzidon in the direction of Gerar as far as Aza, and in the direction of Sedom, Amorah, Admah, and Tzevoyim, as far as Lasha.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">20  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">These are the sons of Cham, by their clans, their languages, their lands, and their nations.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">21  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">To Shem also, the father of all the children of Ever, the older brother of Yafet, children were born.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">22  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The sons of Shem: Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud, and Aram.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">23  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The sons of Aram: Utz, Hul, Geter, and Mash.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">24  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Arpachshad fathered Shelah, and Shelah fathered Ever.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">25  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">To Ever were born two sons: the name of the one was Peleg, for in his days the earth was divided, and his brother's name was Yoktan.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">26  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Yoktan fathered Almodad, Shelef, Hatzarmavet, Yerakh,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">27  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">28  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Oval, Avima'el, Sheva,</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">29  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Ofir, Havilah, and Yovav. All these were the sons of Yoktan.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">30  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The territory in which they lived extended from Mesha in the direction of Sefar to the hill country of the east.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">31  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">These are the sons of Shem, by their clans, their languages, their lands, and their nations.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">32  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">These are the clans of the sons of Noakh, according to their genealogies, in their nations, and from these the nations spread abroad on the earth after the flood.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-top:1px solid #aaaaaa;padding-top:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.905em;font-weight:bold\">COMPARATIVE MANUSCRIPT NOTES</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1A5276;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[DSS]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">4QGend (4Q4) and 4QGene (4Q5) preserve portions of Chapter 10. The Table of Nations is attested in the Cave 4 manuscripts.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1E8449;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[ORIT GE'EZ]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">The Orit Ge'ez preserves Chapter 10 in full. Yovelim Chapters 8-9 provides the most detailed ancient parallel to the Table of Nations — assigning specific geographical territories to each line of Noakh's sons and confirming the division of the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#7D6608;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[MASORETIC VARIANT]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">No significant variants from the DSS in this chapter.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#6E2F8A;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[CRITICAL NOTE]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">Verse 10:6 — the sons of Cham: Kush, Mitzraim, Put, and Kena'an. Kush and Mitzraim are the ancient Hebrew names for the African territories — the lands of modern Ethiopia/Sudan and Egypt respectively. The Table of Nations places the origins of the African peoples within the Cham line, consistent with the geographical division of Yovelim Chapters 8-9 where Cham receives the southern lands including all of Africa.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-bottom:1.5px solid #666666;padding-bottom:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#222222;font-size:1.333em;font-weight:bold\">BERESHIT — CHAPTER 11  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:1.048em;font-style:italic\">The Tower of Bavel — The Dispersion of Languages — The Line to Avram</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">1  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Now the whole earth had one language and the same words.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">2  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And as people migrated from the east, they found a plain in the land of Shinar and settled there.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">3  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And they said to one another: Come, let us make bricks, and burn them thoroughly. And they had brick for stone, and bitumen for mortar.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">4  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Then they said: Come, let us build ourselves a city and a tower with its top in the heavens, and let us make a name for ourselves, lest we be dispersed over the face of the whole earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">5  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And YHWH came down to see the city and the tower, which the children of man had built.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">6  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And YHWH said: Behold, they are one people, and they have all one language, and this is only the beginning of what they will do. And nothing that they propose to do will now be impossible for them.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">7  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Come, let us go down and there confuse their language, so that they may not understand one another's speech.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">8  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">So YHWH dispersed them from there over the face of all the earth, and they left off building the city.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">9  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Therefore its name was called Bavel, because there YHWH confused the language of all the earth. And from there YHWH dispersed them over the face of all the earth.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">10  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">These are the generations of Shem. When Shem was 100 years old, he fathered Arpachshad two years after the flood.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">11  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Shem lived after he fathered Arpachshad 500 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">12  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Arpachshad had lived 35 years, he fathered Shelah.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">13  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Arpachshad lived after he fathered Shelah 403 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">14  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Shelah had lived 30 years, he fathered Ever.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">15  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Shelah lived after he fathered Ever 403 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">16  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Ever had lived 34 years, he fathered Peleg.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">17  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Ever lived after he fathered Peleg 430 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">18  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Peleg had lived 30 years, he fathered Re'u.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">19  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Peleg lived after he fathered Re'u 209 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">20  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Re'u had lived 32 years, he fathered Serug.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">21  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Re'u lived after he fathered Serug 207 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">22  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Serug had lived 30 years, he fathered Nahor.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">23  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Serug lived after he fathered Nahor 200 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">24  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">When Nahor had lived 29 years, he fathered Terach.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">25  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Nahor lived after he fathered Terach 119 years and had other sons and daughters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">26  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">After Terach had lived 70 years, he fathered Avram, Nahor, and Haran.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">27  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Now these are the generations of Terach. Terach fathered Avram, Nahor, and Haran, and Haran fathered Lot.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">28  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Haran died in the presence of his father Terach in the land of his kindred, in Ur of the Kasdim.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">29  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">And Avram and Nahor took wives. The name of Avram's wife was Sarai, and the name of Nahor's wife, Milkah, the daughter of Haran the father of Milkah and Yiskah.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">30  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Now Sarai was barren — she had no child.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">31  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">Terach took Avram his son and Lot the son of Haran, his grandson, and Sarai his daughter-in-law, his son Avram's wife, and they went forth together from Ur of the Kasdim to go into the land of Kena'an, but when they came to Haran, they settled there.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"verse\" style=\"padding-left:1.8em\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.000em;font-weight:bold\">32  </span><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:1.000em\">The days of Terach were 205 years, and Terach died in Haran.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"border-top:1px solid #aaaaaa;padding-top:0.25em\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.905em;font-weight:bold\">COMPARATIVE MANUSCRIPT NOTES</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1A5276;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[DSS]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">4QGena and 4QGenb preserve portions of Chapter 11 including the Tower of Bavel account and the genealogy from Shem to Avram. The Genesis Apocryphon — 1QapGen — expands the account of Avram's family in Aramaic.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#1E8449;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[ORIT GE'EZ]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">The Orit Ge'ez preserves Chapter 11 in full. Yovelim 10:18-26 expands the Bavel account — stating that the evil prince Mastema scattered the nations after YHWH confused the languages, and that only Avram preserved the Hebrew tongue and did not forget it.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#7D6608;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[MASORETIC VARIANT]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">The post-flood genealogy ages in the Masoretic text differ from the Septuagint and other traditions in several cases. Where DSS evidence exists it is followed. For most of this genealogy DSS fragment preservation is partial.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" data-ptype=\"note\" style=\"padding-left:2.4em\"><span style=\"color:#6E2F8A;font-size:0.810em;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic\">[CRITICAL NOTE]  </span><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.810em;font-style:italic\">Verse 11:7 — let us go down and confuse their language. Again the plural divine council. YHWH acts in concert with the heavenly host in the same pattern as Chapter 1:26 and 3:22. The confusing of languages at Bavel is a corporate decision of the divine council — not a unilateral action. The Book of Chanokh and the later traditions associate specific angels with the oversight of specific nations after Bavel.</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#222222;font-size:1.333em;font-weight:bold\">END OF PART ONE — CHAPTERS 1 THROUGH 11</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#444444;font-size:1.048em;font-style:italic\">Volume One — Bereshit — Part One</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#111111;font-size:3.429em;font-weight:bold;font-family:\"Segoe UI Historic\",\"Noto Sans Phoenician\",\"Noto Serif\",\"Arial Unicode MS\",serif\">𐤉𐤄𐤅𐤄</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.952em;font-weight:bold\">IN THE BEGINNING CREATOR CREATED THE HEAVENS AND THE EARTH</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#333333;font-size:0.952em;font-weight:bold\">CHANOKH WALKED WITH CREATOR AND HE WAS NOT FOR CREATOR TOOK HIM</span></p>\n<p class=\"dp\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#555555;font-size:0.857em;font-style:italic\">Bereshit 1:1 and 5:24</span></p>\n"}
